info.name: Solarized Dark: Python documentation
info.description: This style restyles Python's documentation with the dark Solarized color palette.
info.additionalInfo:
This style was tested with the reference manual and the tutorial, but should work for all the documentation. It changes the background color, the text color, but also the colors of the tokens in code snippets (the syntax highlighting) to match the Solarized color palette.

I have recently updated this style to fix some problems with content on some sections of the Python documentation. Everything should look good everywhere, now.
